repo.description: Parse and serialize minecraft packets, plus authentication and encryption.
repo.name: node-minecraft-protocol

body:
Add client-side https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/issues/114 Forge Support

* [x] Send tagged hostname in set_protocol packet
* [x] Receive server channel registrations (FML|HS, FML, FML|MP, FML, FORGE)
* [x] Handle the FML|HS ServerHello with the player's dimension
* [x] Register client plugin channels (FML|HS, FML, FML|MP, FML, FORGE)
* [x] Send the FML|HS ClientHello
* [x] Send client modList
* [x] Receive server modList
* [x] Check client/server mod compatibility - emits `forgeMods` event for app to check
* [x] Send HandshakeAck
* [x] Receive RegistryData packet(s) until hasMore=false
* [x] Send/receive final HandshakeAcks and CompleteHandshake
* [x] Refactor discriminator byte / 'FMLIndexedMessageToMessageCodec' to use a mapper
* [x] Refactor discriminator byte / 'FMLIndexedMessageToMessageCodec' parsing to use one big switch
* [x] Move FML|HS handshake to src/fml.js, support and document forge/forgeMods opts, event
* [x] Refactor into separate module?
* [x] Update for https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/pull/333 Modularization attempt of createClient()
* [x] Move tagHost=\0FML\0 to be installed by src/client/forgeHandshake.js, not the client example

Not included, out of scope for this PR:
* Fully parse the RegistryData packets and emit registry events - would be nice but only needed for advanced usage, can come later
* FORGE plugin channel (observed in packet logging, sends lava and water)
* FML and FML|MP plugin channels (registered, but not seen that they are used at least at login)
* Server-side Forge support https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/issues/114

comment_data.body:
(as I was saying in gitter), it might make more sense to use a big switch+ a mapper, like in https://github.com/PrismarineJS/prismarine-nbt/blob/master/nbt.json#L48 (or https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/blob/master/src/transforms/serializer.js#L21 )
* mapper makes it possible for user to use the names (for example ServerHello instead of 0)
* the big switch probably makes more sense because fields are distinct between each kind of "packet" here
agreed, that's what I wanted to do but couldn't figure out how, to do: investigate those references

commit.message:
Append \0\FML\0 to hostname in set_protocol packet if Forge enabled

http://wiki.vg/User:Pokechu22/Forge#Connection_to_a_forge_server
Create client_forge example copied from client_echo
client_forge example: enable forge
Log registered plugin channels
Parse FML|HS discriminator byte using protodef
Decode fmlProtocolVersion in ServerHello
FML|HS: ServerHello: decode overrideDimension
FML|HS: ServerHello: overrideDimension only sent if fmlProtocolVersion>=2
FML|HS: encode ClientHello
Send ClientHello response to ServerHello

Register client plugin channels on FML|HS ServerHello

This may not be strictly necessary, in either case Forge server with
-Dfml.debugNetworkHandshake=true logs:
[14:26:03] [Netty Server IO #3/INFO] [FML]: Client protocol version 2
FML|HS: ModList: send empty client modlist
FML|HS ModList packet array

Add missing string type in FML|HS serializer

Fixes Error: SizeOf error for mods.2.0.name : missing data type: string
Hardcode a mod list for now
Show FML|HS ModList from server
Send client HandshakeAck with WAITINGSERVERDATA
Complete the HandshakeAck exchange
FML|HS client sends HandshakeAck COMPLETE in response to server
Add a mapper for FML|HS discrminator bytes
Use a mapper for symbolic subpacket names vs discriminator byte values
Switch on packet type through an anonymous container
fmlProtocolVersion client/server no longer collide
ModList field uses 'modid' to match ServerPingList packet JSON
Fix RegistryData hasMore field definition and usage
Fix sending Handshake|Ack phase

Update examples to log when connection is lost

Normally, the client will send a kick packet if the client is
disconnected from the server, but if the connection is lost due to
network or lower-level protocol issues, the 'end' event will be emitted.
Log this event in the examples so it is clear why the scripts exit.
Add forgeMods option, set to array of Forge modifications installed on client
Move to fmlHandshakeStep()

Refactor FML|HS to use state machine

Instead of responding based on the packet type received, maintain a
local state and ensure the correct packets are received. Should help
avoid unexpected states/behavior. See:
https://github.com/ORelio/Minecraft-Console-Client/pull/100/files#diff-65b97c02a9736311374109e22d30ca9cR297
Use symbolic values for writeAck() phase

Forge client example pings server to get forgeMods list

Avoids the need to hardcode the mod list in the client, in order to
successfully connect to arbitrary Forge servers (with various mods).
Move FML|HS to fml.js
fml console.log -> debug
Emit forgeMods event when receiving server's ModList
Add documentation for forge/forgeMods options and forgeMods event

Add tagHost option, clients can use to append to set_protocol serverHost

This is used by Forge clients to tell the server they support FML|HS,
otherwise the server will kick with "you must have FML/Forge installed".
Move FML|HS listener to forge_client example, reduce changes in createClient

Merge branch 'master' into forge (client modularization)

Merging https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/pull/333
Rename src/fml.js -> src/client/forgeHandshake.js
Update client/forgeHandshake.js to be installable as module
Set tagHost in src/client/forgeHandshake.js
Merge branch 'master' into forge
Merge branch 'master' into forge
Integrate Forge support with auto-versioning support
Update var to const/let in forgeHandshake
